      <td><strong>$2,670</strong></td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

The diamonds inside the bezel and prong versions are graded identically: H-I color, SI1-SI2 clarity. You are not getting better stones in the prong version. You are paying more for a different setting style.

> "In earrings, bezel is almost always the right choice for a step-cut stone. The rectangular shape needs a clean frame — and bezel gives you exactly that. You also save thousands compared to the prong version. That money can go toward a heavier carat weight or a second pair entirely." — Farzana Hasan, **[Diamond Critics](https://diamondcritics.com/about-farzana/)**

