## What Each Carat Size Looks Like on the Ear

The emerald cut reads larger than a round stone at the same carat weight. A round 0.5ct stone is approximately 5mm in diameter. A 0.5ct emerald cut stone is approximately 4.7mm × 3.3mm — slightly smaller in diameter but the elongated rectangular face covers more horizontal area. That horizontal spread is what gives it presence at ear level.

This matters for earrings because the face area at ear level is what you see in the mirror and what others see when they look at you. The emerald cut delivers more face coverage per carat than cushion, princess, or round cuts at the same weight.

Here is what each carat weight delivers per ear:

